1. Understand the problem

We are given:

Only the node to delete.
We are NOT given the head of the linked list.

Delete the given node.

Example

Input

Linked List:

4 → 5 → 1 → 9

node = 5

Output

4 → 1 → 9
Another Example

Input

Linked List:

4 → 5 → 1 → 9

node = 1

Output

4 → 5 → 9
2. The tricky part

Normally, to delete a node we do:

previous.next = current.next

Example

1 → 2 → 3 → 4

Delete 3

2.next = 4

Result

1 → 2 → 4

But...

In this problem,

We DON'T have the previous node.

We DON'T have the head.

We ONLY have the node to delete.

So the normal deletion method is impossible.

3. Key Observation

Suppose we have

4 → 5 → 1 → 9

      ↑

    node

We cannot remove node 5 directly.

Instead...

Copy the next node's value into the current node.

Before

4 → 5 → 1 → 9

Copy value

4 → 1 → 1 → 9

Now both nodes contain 1.

Next,

Skip the next node.

node.next = node.next.next;

Picture

Before

1 → 1 → 9

After

1 → 9

Final list

4 → 1 → 9

Looks exactly like node 5 was deleted.

4. Algorithm
Copy the next node's value into the current node.
Skip the next node.
Done.
5. Dry Run

Input

4 → 5 → 1 → 9

Given

node = 5
Step 1

Copy value

node.val = node.next.val;

List becomes

4 → 1 → 1 → 9
Step 2

Delete next node

node.next = node.next.next;

List becomes

4 → 1 → 9

Finished.

6. Why does this work?

We cannot remove the current node because we don't know its previous node.

Instead,

Change the current node's value.
Remove the next node.

From outside, it appears as though the given node has been deleted.

7. Java Code
class Solution {

    public void deleteNode(ListNode node) {

        node.val = node.next.val;

        node.next = node.next.next;
    }
}
8. Time Complexity
O(1)

Only two operations are performed.

9. Space Complexity
O(1)

No extra memory is used.

10. Important Interview Note

This solution works only because the problem guarantees:

The given node is not the last node.
The node to delete always has a next node.

If it were the last node, this approach would fail because there would be no next node to copy from.

11. One-line note for interviews

When you don't have the previous node, you can't delete the current node directly. Instead, copy the next node's value into the current node and delete the next node. 🚀
